oding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/design.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-030 вҖ” Helm Chart Templates and Values\\n2: \\n3: - **AR ID**: AR-030\\n4: - **Module**: manifests\\n5: - **Language**: YAML\\n6: - **Size**: L\\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\\n8: - **Stage**: ST-1\\n9: \\n10: ## 1. Architecture\\n11: \\n12: ### 1.1 Overview\\n13: \\n14: The AgentCube Helm chart provides a declarative, reusable deployment mechanism for Kubernetes clusters. The chart packages Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, RBAC resources, and CRDs into a single installable unit with configurable values.\\n15: \\n16: ### 1.2 Chart Structure\\n17: \\n18: ```\\n19: manifests/charts/base/\\n20: в”ңв”Җв”Җ Chart.yaml\\n21: в”ңв”Җв”Җ values.yaml\\n22: в”ңв”Җв”Җ crds/\\n23: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\\n24: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\\n25: в””в”Җв”Җ templates/\\n26:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ _helpers.tpl\\n27:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ workloadmanager.yaml\\n28:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentcube-router.yaml\\n29:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ rbac/\\n30:     в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ workloadmanager.yaml\\n31:     в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ router.yaml\\n32:     в””в”Җв”Җ volcano/\\n33:         в””в”Җв”Җ agent-scheduler.yaml\\n34: ```\\n35: \\n36: ### 1.3 Components\\n37: \\n38: | Component | Kind | Required | Description |\\n39: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\\n40: | Workload Manager | Deployment + Service | Yes | Agent session management |\\n41: | Router | Deployment + Service | Yes | API routing lay...\n  Line 22: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775871601541,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a32274b001SoW33vTp66h0hf\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a32183800130vJ34ZKN0FQOC\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285ce6281ffekEVhHvlf3nPcA5\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_48a89efada3b4f7891cd8ce6\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/spec.md\",\"limit\":50},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Deployment Specification\\n2: \\n3: ## Purpose\\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\\n5: \\n6: ## Requirements\\n7: \\n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\\n10: \\n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\\n15: \\n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\\n18: \\n19: #### Scena...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-030_ST-3.log:\n  Line 20: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775871558592,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a30b52b0019tTgX0um87ls23\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a30a9ae0010jlW9biSrcsUzO\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285cfc9c5ffeHtJE1OVlfRDcQ3\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_f9d3d68f8cc64d77aa43dbfd\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# AR-030 вҖ” Helm Chart Templates and Values\\n\\n- **AR ID**: AR-030\\n- **Module**: manifests\\n- **Language**: YAML\\n- **Size**: L\\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\\n- **Stage**: ST-1\\n\\n## 1. Architecture\\n\\n### 1.1 Overview\\n\\nThe AgentCube Helm chart provides a declarative, reusable deployment mechanism for Kubernetes clusters. The chart packages Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, RBAC resources, and CRDs into a single installable unit with configurable values.\\n\\n### 1.2 Chart Structure\\n\\n```\\nmanifests/charts/base/\\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ Chart.yaml\\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ values.yaml\\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ crds/\\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\\nв””в”Җв”Җ templates/\\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ _helpers.tpl\\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ workloadmanager.yaml\\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentcube-router.yaml\\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ rbac/\\n    в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ workloadmanager.yaml\\n    в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ router.yaml\\n    в””в”Җв”Җ volcano/\\n        в””в”Җв”Җ agent-scheduler.yaml\\n```\\n\\n### 1.3 Components\\n\\n| Component | Kind | Required | Description |\\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\\n| Workload Manager | Deployment + Service | Yes | Agent session management |\\n| Router | Deployment + Service | Yes | API routing layer |\\n| WorkloadManager RBAC | ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding | Yes | Cluster-wide permissions |\\n| Router RBAC | ServiceAccount + Role + RoleBinding | Optional | Namespace-scoped permissions |\\n| Volcano Scheduler | Multiple (SA, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) | Optional | Custom scheduler |\\n| CRDs | CustomResourceDefinition | Yes | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter |\\n\\n## 2. Data Structures\\n\\n### 2....\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-030_ST-2.log:\n  Line 17: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775871378237,\"sessionID\":\"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7a2ec02f001BoIE8wef6xt5fM\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d7a2eb4cb001gaDtSgysobxilX\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_285d27a16ffe0wLYGNrj8mZFua\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_7a86f6cd438a4fd2af2f1a62\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/spec.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Deployment Specification\\n2: \\n3: ## Purpose\\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\\n5: \\n6: ## Requirements\\n7: \\n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\\n10: \\n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\\n15: \\n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\\n17: The sys