verview\\n4: \\n5: This design document describes the implementation of JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication and issuance for the agentcube router component. The router will serve as both a JWT issuer for clients and a validator for incoming JWT-authenticated requests, providing secure communication between clients, router, and workload manager.\\n6: \\n7: ## Background\\n8: \\n9: The router component acts as a gateway between external clients and agent runtimes/code interpreters managed by the workload manager. Currently, JWT tokens are generated for outbound requests to the workload manager but there is no JWT validation for incoming client requests. This implementation adds complete JWT authentication capabilities to the router.\\n10: \\n11: ## Architecture\\n12: \\n13: ### Components\\n14: \\n15: ```\\n16: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ         JWT Token         в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\\n17: в”Ӯ   Client    в”Ӯ в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә   в”Ӯ   Router    в”Ӯ\\n18: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                           в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\\n19:      в–І                                            в”Ӯ\\n20:      в”Ӯ                                            в”Ӯ JWT Token\\n21:      в”Ӯ                                            в”Ӯ (Signed with Router Keys)\\n22:      в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\\n23:                                   ...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z_logs/AR-019_ST-3.log:\n  Line 12: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775863174392,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2864e9e5fffeybhtzWMXF9IT3H\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79b1904f001oMUQD1ew78X1MK\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79b18000001qRLApdAiZeQd8n\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2864e9e5fffeybhtzWMXF9IT3H\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"